BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KL32oYM1XDKSZ7BrkYLY4
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260314T153654Z
DTSTART:20260324T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-24T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NqzfjtVPhvidIt8zkQCR_
SUMMARY:Mindfulness Walk | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260314T153654Z
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Mindfulness Walk\n\nTaking inspiration from the Japanese idea  
	of shinrin-yoku \\(forest bathing\\)\, we will be hosting a series of mind
	fulness walks in Pioneer Park. Mindfulness walking in the forest has shown
	 to  have a myriad of benefits from improving heart health to reducing str
	ess  \\(https://www.npr.org/2023/08/22/1195337204/a-guide-to-forest-bathin
	g\\).\n\n \n\nForest Steward Marilyn Cornwell \\(https://www.soulscapes.us
	/\\) will be lea ding an hour-long guided walk through the park. Please jo
	in us if your cur ious about mindfulness\, want to learn more about and ex
	perience healing powers of being in nature\, and/or if you want to deepen 
	your connection with Pioneer Park and others.\n\nWhen:  Tuesday\, March 24
	th\, 11am-12pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park SE\, Meet at the corner of Island Cr
	est Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNTEER EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dre
	ss for the weather in  clothes and shoes you will comfortable walking and 
	standing in\, as well as water. \n\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup.
	org/9XTJA\n\n\n\n \n\nOpens in new window\n\nPDF Download\n\nWord Download
	\n\nExcel Download \n\nPowerPoint Download\n\nDocument Download\n\nhttps:/
	/seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mindfulness-walk-pioneer-park/18066
	425/2026-03-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mindfulness-walk-pioneer-
	park/18066425/2026-03-24T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
